lessfs requires tokyocabinet's tcutil library (TCTREE)
to be installed on the system for in-memory caching.
http://tokyocabinet.sourceforge.net/index.html

lessfs uses lmdb as its database backend.
BerkeleyDB is still supported but no longer preferred.

As backend storage for the data chunk_io with o_direct is recommended.

To build from source:
./configure (defaults to using lmdb).
make
make install
